formula: Expansion of 5 + eta(q)^5*eta(q^3)/(eta(q^2)*eta(q^6)^5) in powers of q.
mathematica: QP = QPochhammer; s = 5*q + QP[q]^5*(QP[q^3]/(QP[q^2]*QP[q^6]^5)) + O[q]^50; CoefficientList[s, q] (* _Jean-François Alcover_, Nov 15 2015 *)
